	;;;; SWITCH DISTANCE SETTING ;;;
	
	;;; This crucial setting controls the distance in which a-life enters its 'online mode'. Beyond it, NPCs are 'offline', which means they are only simulated in memory and thus will not be visible and combat with them will be impossible. Vanilla value is 150, but Misery has been specially tuned - through scripts and tweaks - to operate on a distance of 300 and higher. You can increase the number as much as you like, but bear in mind that this will require a high-end rig, or lower it to ensure a better performance of the mod at the cost of immersion.
	
    switch_distance				= 300 ; 950 ; 150 ; 350 ; 450 ; 500 ; 550 ; 600 ; 850 metres
	
